John Elder and Armin T. Wegner documented the horrific suffering endured by Armenians by Ottoman Turks .
They helped build a case against a Turkish government which still denies genocide .
In one image, two Armenians are pictured hanging in the street in broad daylight in the capital, Istanbul .
The images were taken by John Elder, a volunteer military nurse .
He was arrested and put to work in cholera wards in Baghdad at the request of the Turkish government .